window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>One of the most influential authors from Russiaâ€™s Golden Age, Fyodor Dostoevsky left behind a vast collection of prized literary works, including <i>Crime and Punishment</i> and <i>The Brothers Karamazov</i>. </p> <p>In <i>The Idiot</i>, Prince Myshkin possesses a childlike innocence and trusting nature that leave him vulnerable to abuse by those around him. Returning to St. Petersburg to collect an inheritance, Myshkin realizes he is a stranger in a society obsessed with wealth, manipulation and power. </p>"; 
